{
  "text": "A similar analysis was performed by [CITATION_1] . However, they considered that the roughness Reynolds number (Re * ) could be neglected for turbulent flow in rough channels, such as the natural channels.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "129378164"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "129378164": {
      "title": "Predicting longitudinal dispersion coefficient in natural streams",
      "abstract": "In this study, previous empirical equations used to compute the dispersion coefficient are analyzed in order to evaluate their behavior in predicting dispersion characteristics in natural streams. A comparative analysis of previous theoretical and empirical equations is reported. A new simplified method for predicting dispersion coefficients using hydraulic and geometric data that are easily obtained in natural streams is also developed. The one-step Huber method, which is one of the nonlinear multiregression methods, is applied to derive a new dispersion coefficient equation. This equation is proven to be superior in explaining dispersion characteristics of natural streams more precisely, as compared to existing equations."
    }
  }
}